replace() method==>
               This method is used to replace a part of a given string with a new substring.
This method searches for specified regular expression in a given string  and then replace it if the match occurs.
syntax==>         str.replace(oldstring,newstring);
Example==>
<html>
<body>
<script type="text/javascript">
var  str="This is javascript class";
document.write("Original string:"+str);
var str1=str.replace("javascript","Angularscript");
document.write("<br>New string:"+str1);
</script>
</body>
</html>
